[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 7107,
        "end_time": 10170,
        "text": "Humans know the surprising prick\nof a needle,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 10170,
        "end_time": 12539,
        "text": "the searing pain of a stubbed toe,"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 12539,
        "end_time": 14969,
        "text": "and the throbbing of a toothache."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 14969,
        "end_time": 19600,
        "text": "We can identify many types of pain\nand have multiple ways of treating it."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 19600,
        "end_time": 21850,
        "text": "But what about other species?"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 21850,
        "end_time": 26070,
        "text": "How do the animals all around us\nexperience pain?"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 26070,
        "end_time": 28230,
        "text": "It&#39;s important that we find out."
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 28230,
        "end_time": 29851,
        "text": "We keep animals as pets,"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 29851,
        "end_time": 31460,
        "text": "they enrich our environment,"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 31460,
        "end_time": 33631,
        "text": "we farm many species for food,"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 33631,
        "end_time": 37781,
        "text": "and we use them in experiments\nto advance science and human health."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 37781,
        "end_time": 39830,
        "text": "Animals are clearly important to us,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 39830,
        "end_time": 44462,
        "text": "so it&#39;s equally important that we avoid\ncausing them unnecessary pain."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 44462,
        "end_time": 47111,
        "text": "For animals that are similar to us,\nlike mammals,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 47111,
        "end_time": 50281,
        "text": "it&#39;s often obvious when they&#39;re hurting."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 50281,
        "end_time": 52521,
        "text": "But there&#39;s a lot that isn&#39;t obvious,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 52521,
        "end_time": 56201,
        "text": "like whether pain relievers that work\non us also help them."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 56201,
        "end_time": 58121,
        "text": "And the more different \nan animal is from us,"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 58121,
        "end_time": 61195,
        "text": "the harder it is to understand \ntheir experience."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 61195,
        "end_time": 63802,
        "text": "How do you tell whether \na shrimp is in pain?"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 63802,
        "end_time": 65131,
        "text": "A snake?"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 65131,
        "end_time": 66691,
        "text": "A snail?"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 66691,
        "end_time": 69272,
        "text": "In vertebrates, including humans,"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 69272,
        "end_time": 72482,
        "text": "pain can be split \ninto two distinct processes."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 72482,
        "end_time": 76560,
        "text": "In first, nerves and the skin sense\nsomething harmful"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 76560,
        "end_time": 79195,
        "text": "and communicate that information\nto the spinal cord."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 79195,
        "end_time": 81784,
        "text": "There, motor neurons activate movements"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 81784,
        "end_time": 84682,
        "text": "that make us rapidly \njerk away from the threat."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 84682,
        "end_time": 88322,
        "text": "This is the physical recognition of harm\ncalled nociception,"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 88322,
        "end_time": 89578,
        "text": "and nearly all animals,"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 89578,
        "end_time": 92297,
        "text": "even those with very simple \nnervous systems,"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 92297,
        "end_time": 93765,
        "text": "experience it."
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 93765,
        "end_time": 96752,
        "text": "Without this ability, animals would be\nunable to avoid harm"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 96752,
        "end_time": 99736,
        "text": "and their survival would be threatened."
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 99736,
        "end_time": 103455,
        "text": "The second part is the conscious\nrecognition of harm."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 103455,
        "end_time": 106593,
        "text": "In humans, this occurs when the sensory\nneurons in our skin"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 106593,
        "end_time": 111395,
        "text": "make a second round of connections\nvia the spinal cord to the brain."
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 111395,
        "end_time": 117022,
        "text": "There, millions of neurons in multiple\nregions create the sensations of pain."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 117022,
        "end_time": 121152,
        "text": "For us, this is a very complex experience\nassociated with emotions like fear,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 121152,
        "end_time": 122082,
        "text": "panic,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 122082,
        "end_time": 123212,
        "text": "and stress,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 123212,
        "end_time": 125734,
        "text": "which we can communicate to others."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 125734,
        "end_time": 128483,
        "text": "But it&#39;s harder to know exactly\nhow animals experience"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 128483,
        "end_time": 130592,
        "text": "this part of the process"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 130592,
        "end_time": 133892,
        "text": "because most them can&#39;t show us\nwhat they feel."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 133892,
        "end_time": 138543,
        "text": "However, we get clues from observing\nhow animals behave."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 138543,
        "end_time": 142493,
        "text": "Wild, hurt animals are known\nto nurse their wounds,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 142493,
        "end_time": 144674,
        "text": "make noises to show their distress,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 144674,
        "end_time": 147033,
        "text": "and become reclusive."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 147033,
        "end_time": 151154,
        "text": "In the lab, scientists have discovered\nthat animals like chickens and rats"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 151154,
        "end_time": 155633,
        "text": "will self-administer pain-reducing\ndrugs if they&#39;re hurting."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 155633,
        "end_time": 159184,
        "text": "Animals also avoid situations where\nthey&#39;ve been hurt before,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 159184,
        "end_time": 162383,
        "text": "which suggests awareness of threats."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 162383,
        "end_time": 165204,
        "text": "We&#39;ve reached the point that research\nhas made us so sure"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 165204,
        "end_time": 167124,
        "text": "that vertebrates recognize pain"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 167124,
        "end_time": 171634,
        "text": "that it&#39;s illegal in many countries\nto needlessly harm these animals."
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 171634,
        "end_time": 176054,
        "text": "But what about other types of animals\nlike invertebrates?"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 176054,
        "end_time": 178313,
        "text": "These animals aren&#39;t legally protected,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 178313,
        "end_time": 182234,
        "text": "partly because their behaviors\nare harder to read."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 182234,
        "end_time": 184436,
        "text": "We can make good guesses\nabout some of them,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 184436,
        "end_time": 185274,
        "text": "like oysters,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 185274,
        "end_time": 186104,
        "text": "worms,"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 186104,
        "end_time": 187324,
        "text": "and jellyfish."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 187324,
        "end_time": 189885,
        "text": "These are examples of animals\nthat either lack a brain"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 189885,
        "end_time": 192225,
        "text": "or have a very simple one."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 192225,
        "end_time": 196126,
        "text": "So an oyster may recoil when squirted\nwith lemon juice, for instance,"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 196126,
        "end_time": 198815,
        "text": "because of nociception."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 198815,
        "end_time": 200725,
        "text": "But with such a simple nervous system,"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 200725,
        "end_time": 204525,
        "text": "it&#39;s unlikely to experience \nthe conscious part of pain."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 204525,
        "end_time": 207475,
        "text": "Other invertebrate animals \nare more complicated, though,"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 207475,
        "end_time": 208805,
        "text": "like the octopus,"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 208805,
        "end_time": 210305,
        "text": "which has a sophisticated brain"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 210305,
        "end_time": 214235,
        "text": "and is thought to be one of the most \nintelligent invertebrate animals."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 214235,
        "end_time": 219686,
        "text": "Yet, in many countries, people continue\nthe practice of eating live octopus."
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 219686,
        "end_time": 223905,
        "text": "We also boil live crawfish, shrimp, \nand crabs"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 223905,
        "end_time": 227125,
        "text": "even though we don&#39;t really know\nhow they&#39;re affected either."
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 227125,
        "end_time": 228997,
        "text": "This poses an ethical problem"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 228997,
        "end_time": 232905,
        "text": "because we may be causing these animals\nunnecessary suffering."
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 232905,
        "end_time": 237036,
        "text": "Scientific experimentation,\nthough controversial, gives us some clues."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 237036,
        "end_time": 241378,
        "text": "Tests on hermit crabs show that they&#39;ll\nleave an undesirable shell"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 241378,
        "end_time": 243497,
        "text": "if they&#39;re zapped with electricity"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 243497,
        "end_time": 245806,
        "text": "but stay if it&#39;s a good shell."
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 245806,
        "end_time": 249257,
        "text": "And octopi that may originally curl up\nan injured arm to protect it"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 249257,
        "end_time": 252307,
        "text": "will risk using it to catch prey."
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 252307,
        "end_time": 256826,
        "text": "That suggests that these animals make\nvalue judgements around sensory input"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 256826,
        "end_time": 260296,
        "text": "instead of just reacting \nreflexively to harm."
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 260296,
        "end_time": 263897,
        "text": "Meanwhile, crabs have been known\nto repeatedly rub a spot on their bodies"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 263897,
        "end_time": 266687,
        "text": "where they&#39;ve received an electric shock."
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 266687,
        "end_time": 268567,
        "text": "And even sea slugs flinch"
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 268567,
        "end_time": 271896,
        "text": "when they know they&#39;re about \nto receive a noxious stimulus."
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 271896,
        "end_time": 275979,
        "text": "That means they have some memory\nof physical sensations."
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 275979,
        "end_time": 278368,
        "text": "We still have a lot to learn about\nanimal pain."
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 278368,
        "end_time": 280387,
        "text": "As our knowledge grows,"
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 280387,
        "end_time": 285127,
        "text": "it may one day allow us to live in a world\nwhere we don&#39;t cause pain needlessly."
    }
]